Hi all,
My team is trying to reduce the amount of data we are transmitting over our CAN Bus by adding a Canivore and running our swerve subsystem through it. We are using Kraken Swerve Drive with CTRE CanCoders and a Pigeon, and are using the CTRE Phoenix-generated Swerve Library. I cannot figure out how to specify the CAN Bus name in the library. I can’t even find where the motors are defined. How do you specify the name? I would put our mechanisms on the Canivore instead, but all our other hardware is Rev.
Thanks for the help

UPDATE: I have resolved this. After calling CTRE. In file called “Tuner Constants”, a ‘SwerveDrivetrainConstants’ object is initialized. Calling the ‘.withCanBusName(“name”) method on it will specify the CAN Bus name. This object is passed into the swerve drivetrain. In the default file generated by CTRE, this is already put in place. You just have to change the name.
Hope this helps anyone with the same question!
